('rec22lTM5lpQa6Kpy','Enbridge','Major Player','Midstream Energy / Gas Transmission / Renewable Power','utility_iou','Public','Calgary, AB, Canada','ENB','https://www.enbridge.com','https://www.linkedin.com/company/enbridge',null,null,null,null,null,'Different strategic posture than Williams — leans on connectivity to ~45% of all US gas-fired generation rather than vertical integration into BTM gen. Three-business optionality (Gas Transmission + Gas Distribution + Renewable Power) lets them serve grid-side AND tech-company offtake (Meta deals are renewable-PPA structured, not BTM gas). North American footprint (incl. Canadian gas distribution) provides cross-border DC siting optionality not available to US-only midstream peers.','Greg Ebel',null,null,'C$53B+ (FY2025)','~C$130B market cap',null,null,null,null,null,'Gas transmission + renewable PPAs',null,'Advancing 50+ data center opportunities across North America requiring up to 10 Bcf/d of new takeaway capacity in proximity to existing Gas Transmission assets. Gas utilities portfolio sees 40+ opportunities for ~3 Bcf/d new demand through 2030 (~C$4B investment potential), of which ~1.5 Bcf/d is late/mid-stage DC development. Secured backlog grew to $39B (FY2025). Expected to sanction additional power gen + DC projects through 2026.','Largest energy infrastructure company in North America by enterprise value. Gas transmission network within 50 miles of 40+ Bcf/d of DC + power-gen opportunities, area containing ~30 planned DCs and 80+ GW of coal-to-gas transition opportunities. Sanctioned in FY2025: Cowboy Phase 1 (365 MW solar + 135 MW BESS expandable to 200 MW, Wyoming, US$1.2B, Meta PPA); Easter (152 MW onshore wind, Amarillo TX, US$0.4B, Meta PPA); Bay Runner extension to Whistler Pipeline; Eiger Express upsized 2.5→3.7 Bcf/d. Reaffirmed 2026 financial guidance Feb 2026; secured backlog grew to $39B. Plans ~$3B/yr ongoing growth capex across utilities. Forecasts NA gas demand growing double-digits through 2040 with up to 65 Bcf/d total opportunity set.','Meta (750+ MW under construction across Cowboy Phase 1 solar+BESS in Wyoming and Easter wind in Texas — both supporting Meta DC operations under long-term PPAs, ISD 2027); ~200 MW additional DC supply contracted, 600 MW under evaluation',null,'["D2 — Power & Energy", "D4 — M&A & Capital Markets", "D6 — New Entrants"]'::jsonb,'Multiple Sources','2026-04-30'::date),
