('rec9KyxlIGqy2B0yI','Samsung Foundry','Major Player','Semiconductor / Contract Foundry / IDM','oem_supply_chain','Public','Suwon, South Korea (+ Taylor, TX USA)','005930 (KRX) / Samsung Electronics','https://semiconductor.samsung.com/foundry',null,null,null,null,null,null,'Samsung Foundry is the third major leading-edge chipmaker alongside TSMC and Intel Foundry. Samsung was the first foundry to deploy GAA transistors commercially (SF3E, 2022) but persistent yield problems with GAA-based nodes have limited adoption to niche applications (crypto ASICs). The highest-performing Samsung chips in production are still made on FinFET-based SF4P and SF4X. SF2 entered mass production mid-2025 but is considered limited adoption. SF2P (2nd-gen 2nm) is a 2026 priority focus. The iterative SF2 family (SF2 → SF2P → SF2X → SF2Z with BSPDN) signals yield-first, not scaling-first, philosophy. SF1.4 (1.4nm-class, 2027) is Samsung''s headline next node — consumer/smartphone-optimized without BSPDN. SF1.4 is positioned above SF3/SF2 families, possibly featuring a new GAA transistor design. EUV pellicle strategy at SF1.4 is unresolved and is the single largest yield risk for the node. Taylor, Texas fab targeting 50,000 wafer starts per month in risk production 2026 with new production flows and potential pellicle adoption.',null,null,null,'Part of Samsung Electronics (~$200B+ revenue total)',null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,'SF2 HVM mid-2025 (limited). SF2P / SF2X 2026 (yield recovery phase). SF2A / SF2Z 2027. SF1.4 mass production 2027 (1.4nm-class, no BSPDN). Taylor TX fab 2026 risk production, 50k WSPM target. EUV pellicle adoption decision pending — structural yield risk for SF1.4.','SF2 mass production mid-2025 (1st-gen 2nm GAA). SF2P 2026 (2nd-gen 2nm). SF2X 2026 (HPC-oriented). SF2A 2027 (automotive). SF2Z 2027 (SF2X + BSPDN). SF1.4 mass production 2027 — 1.4nm-class, consumer/smartphone-optimized, no BSPDN. Pellicle question: lack of EUV pellicles remains unresolved into SF1.4; drives stochastic mask defect risk. Taylor TX fab targeting 2026 risk production with pellicles and new production flows at 50k WSPM. Yield improvement is stated top priority over node scaling.','Samsung LSI (internal), limited external HPC; historically Qualcomm, Tesla FSD, Google TPU (lost to TSMC)',null,'["D1 — Chips & Density"]'::jsonb,'Airtable Tracking Companies','2026-05-17'::date),
