('recQ6Z5iy5j48BPIT','Intel','Major Player','Semiconductor / IDM / Foundry','oem_supply_chain','Public','Santa Clara, CA','INTC',null,null,null,null,null,null,null,'Integrated Device Manufacturer (IDM) and foundry. Intel Foundry is pursuing the most architecturally ambitious leading-edge roadmap among the three major foundries, combining GAA RibbonFET transistors with PowerVia backside power delivery (BSPDN) simultaneously — a first in the industry. 18A node entered high-volume manufacturing H2 2025 at Oregon development lines; Arizona production lines ongoing. 14A and 14A-E target 2027–2028 production readiness with 2nd Gen RibbonFET GAA, revamped PowerDirect BSPDN, Turbo Cells, and High-NA EUV lithography. 14A claims 25–35% power improvement and 15–20% performance improvement over 18A at 1.3x density. Key risk: world-class yields not expected until 2027; 20A node was abruptly cancelled late 2024. No automotive or smartphone customers currently. Apple reportedly struck preliminary agreement for Intel to make some chips. Elon Musk''s Terafab project set to license Intel 14A for AI chip manufacturing (SpaceX as manufacturer). 18A-P variant (2027) targets 9% more performance and 18% better thermal conductivity. 18A-PT adds through-silicon via support for 3D-integrated SiP. Intel 16 and UMC 12 mature nodes maintained for revenue diversification.','Lip-Bu Tan',null,null,'~$53B (FY2025 est.)',null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,'18A HVM H2 2025. 18A-P 2027 (+9% perf, +18% thermal conductivity). 14A / 14A-E 2028 production readiness (High-NA EUV, PowerDirect BSPDN, 2nd Gen RibbonFET). Terafab 14A licensing (SpaceX manufacturing). Apple preliminary manufacturing deal. SK Hynix EMIB partnership (HBM integration). Intel 16 / UMC 12 mature node revenue floor.','18A node in HVM H2 2025 (Oregon). 18A-P enhanced variant 2027. 14A / 14A-E 2028 (first Intel node with High-NA EUV). Terafab / SpaceX 14A licensing deal. Apple preliminary chip manufacturing agreement. SK Hynix partnership reports (EMIB 2.5D HBM integration). Global semiconductor foundry market hit $320B record in 2025; TSMC grew 4x faster than rivals. Intel foundry zero automotive/smartphone customers — a strategic gap vs TSMC and Samsung.',null,null,'["D1 — Chips & Density"]'::jsonb,'Airtable Tracking Companies','2026-05-17'::date),
