('reccpBCR94rwCmJQJ','Accenture','Major Player','Global Consulting / Systems Integrator — Infrastructure & Capital Projects','investor_pe','Public','Dublin, Ireland','ACN','https://www.accenture.com',null,null,null,null,null,null,'The most aggressive strategic acquirer in the AI data center consulting and capital projects space. Since 2023 has executed a systematic global rollup: Anser Advisory (US), Comtech (Canada), BOSLAN (Spain), IQT Group (Italy), Soben (UK), Partners in Performance (Australia), Orlade (France), DLB Associates (US — 620 employees, $XXM), Verum Partners (Brazil, Feb 2026), and Ookla (March 2026 — first true data/telemetry acquisition). The Ookla deal is the inflection: the playbook has evolved from ''buy services bodies'' to ''buy data layers feeding AI-driven optimization.'' Geographic gaps remaining: DACH (Germany), Nordics, Middle East, India, SE Asia. Capability gaps remaining: dedicated power/grid advisory, deep liquid cooling thermal engineering, nuclear/SMR program management, skilled trades workforce. Big 4 / consulting peers (EY, PwC, McKinsey) are NOT running comparable plays — auditor independence rules and partnership structures constrain them. Accenture is functionally alone in this lane.',null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,'Industry X practice (where capital projects acquisitions land). End-to-end data center capability buildout: site selection (DLB), construction management (Soben, Anser, Verum), program management (Comtech, IQT, Orlade), net-zero infra (BOSLAN), operational optimization (Partners in Performance), network telemetry (Ookla).','Apr 2026 — Accenture announced acquisition of Verum Partners (Brazil) on Feb 24, 2026, and Ookla on Mar 3, 2026. Faraday read: next 2–3 acquisitions will fill the power/grid advisory gap and the liquid cooling/thermal engineering gap. The Ookla precedent makes a DCIM software acquisition newly plausible.',null,null,'["D4 — M&A & Capital Markets", "D10 — Construction",