('recfowzHOVsYQCV1G','TSMC','Major Player','Semiconductor / Contract Foundry','oem_supply_chain','Public','Hsinchu, Taiwan','TSM','https://www.tsmc.com',null,null,null,null,null,null,'Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company — the world''s largest and most commercially disciplined contract chipmaker. TSMC initiated high-volume manufacturing of N2 (2nm-class, first GAA nanosheet node) simultaneously at two Taiwan fabs in December 2025, an unprecedented scale of simultaneous ramp driven by AI demand. Customers include Apple, AMD, NVIDIA, Intel (packaging), and Qualcomm. N2 is the first TSMC node with GAA nanosheet transistors. Roadmap is segment-bifurcated: high-performance computing (HPC) nodes receive Backside Power Delivery Network (BSPDN/SuperPowerRail); smartphone/cost-sensitive nodes do not. A16 (2027) adds SPR BSPDN on top of N2P for HPC. A14 (2028) targets smartphones without BSPDN, then re-emerges with BSPDN for data center in 2029. A13 (2029) and A12 (2029) extend the roadmap to 2nd-gen GAA. Global semiconductor foundry market was $320B in 2025; TSMC grew 4x faster than rivals. TSMC has warned publicly that it views Intel Foundry as a formidable competitor. TSMC SoIC 3D stacking roadmap targets 4.5-micron pitch by 2029 (from 6-micron today). Arizona fab expansion: $20B allocated, faces water and labor shortages exacerbated by visa constraints.','C.C. Wei',null,null,'~$90B (FY2025 est.)',null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,'N2 HVM Dec 2025 (simultaneous dual-fab ramp). N2P + A16 2027 (HPC vs. cost split). A14 2028 (smartphone) / A14+BSPDN 2029 (data center). A13 / A12 2029 (2nd-gen GAA). SoIC 3D 4.5-micron pitch 2029. $20B Arizona expansion. EPYC Venice (AMD), Apple A-series, NVIDIA Blackwell/Rubin as anchor N2 customers.','N2 HVM Dec 2025 (two fabs simultaneously). N2P 2027 (frontside power). A16 2027 (BSPDN / SPR). N2X / N2U 2027 (HPC and density variants). A14 2028 smartphone node. A14 with BSPDN 2029 data center node. A13 2029 (+6% logic density over A14). A12 2029 (2nd-gen GAA, denser than A16). SoIC 3D stacking: 6-micron today → 4.5-micron 2029. $20B Arizona expansion (water/labor constraints). TSMC warned investors it views Intel Foundry as formidable. Foundry market $320B record 2025.','Apple, NVIDIA, AMD, Qualcomm, Broadcom, Intel (packaging)',null,'["D1 — Chips & Density"]'::jsonb,'Airtable Tracking Companies','2026-05-17'::date),
